<div id="instruction">	
	Tips for Phase 2 of the IELTS speaking test - your 1-2 minute talk.
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/set6_02.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  
<div id="presentation">  
  <h6>Tip 1</h6>
  <p>Read what is required. Try and think of at last two things to say for each question.</p>
  
  <h6>Tip 2</h6>
  <p>Don't say you cannot talk about the topic. </p>
  
  <h6>Tip 3</h6>
  <p>Don't go off the topic.</p>
  
  <h6>Tip 4</h6>
  <p>Don't wait to be prompted by the examiner.</p>
  
  <h6>Tip 5</h6>
  <p>Show that you are willing to discuss anything, even if you know very little about it. Use your strategies to 'talk round' it.</p>
  
  <h6>Tip 6</h6>
  <p>Give your own opinion about the question and ideas.</p>
